notes.text:
This update for ffmpeg fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2019-13390: Fixed a potential crash when processing a crafted AVI stream (bsc#1140754).
- CVE-2022-3341: Fixed a potential crash when processing a crafted NUT stream (bsc#1206778).
- CVE-2022-48434: Fixed use after free in libavcodec/pthread_frame.c (bsc#1209934).

notes.text: A null pointer dereference issue was discovered in 'FFmpeg' in decode_main_header() function of libavformat/nutdec.c file. The flaw occurs because the function lacks check of the return value of avformat_new_stream() and triggers the null pointer dereference error, causing an application to crash.
